properties.headline: Hydrologic Outlook issued January 13 at 4:20PM AKST by NWS Anchorage AK
properties.description:
Work is still being done in the area, but for the most part the
ice has been cleared up. This will be the last statement for this
event unless conditions change.

The Matanuska Borough has been responding to the flooding on
Willow Creek and maintains a website for updated information on
road conditions and access. Please check this website for current
updates on the conditions near Deneki Road:
https://www.matsugov.us/spotlights/willow-creke-flooding-2019

The Borough has also been posting updates to their Facebook page:
https://www.facebook.com/MatSuBorough

NWSheadline: ICE JAM FLOODING HAS ENDED ON WILLOW CREEK UPSTREAM OF THE DENEKI ROAD BRIDGE
